p.m:
\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
    20\cdot\left( -{\frac{6}{5}} \right)
    \amp =\frac{20}{1} \cdot \left(-{\frac{6}{5}}\right) \amp \hbox{We can divide both the first numerator and the second denominator by 5.}\\
    \amp =\frac{4}{1} \cdot \left(-{\frac{6}{1}}\right)\\
    \amp ={-24}
    \end{aligned}}
